         <listPlace>
            <place xml:id="place-000077" type="site">
               <placeName xml:id="name000077-1" type="site-name" xml:lang="en">Qinshui Shundi Temple</placeName>
               <placeName xml:id="name000077-2" type="site-name" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin">Qinshui Shundimiao </placeName>
               <placeName xml:id="name000077-3" type="site-name" xml:lang="zh-Hant">沁水舜帝廟</placeName>
               <placeName xml:id="name000077-4" type="site-name" xml:lang="zh-Hans">沁水舜帝庙</placeName>
               <idno type="URI">https://architecturasinica.org/place/000077</idno>
               <desc type="site-data" source="#bibl000077-1">
                  Date founded unknown. According to a stele fragment inside the temple, repairs were made in the Qing dynasty (宣统二年 (1910)). The temple site encompasses 684 square meters. The complex faces south with a single courtyard, axial buildings include a Mountain Gate and main hall; on the east and west are side halls of 6 bays each. Within the compound, other than the Jin dynasty main hall, the rest of the buildings are Qing dynasty. (Translation Lydia Ohl, ed. T. Miller)
               </desc>
               <note>Site geolocated in this entry was lacking a Mountain Gate, and the main hall departs from the description given in the Zhongguo wenwu dituji cited above. Location needs verification.</note>
               <state type="existence" subtype="dynasty" source="#bibl000077-2" from="1115" to="1912">
